commits.commitMessage:
Use --entrypoint

If the entrypoint of the Docker image is defined, it would not work
well, and using --entrypoint through DOCKER_ENCAPS_ARGS is not doing
too well with unconfigurable 'tail -f /dev/null'.

- Defining:
  DOCKER_ENCAPS_ENTRYPOINT: used for --entrypoint, defaults to 'tail'
  DOCKER_ENCAPS_SLEEP_CMD: used as command

- Combined, this forces the image to do 'tail -f /dev/null', same as
  before

Resolves: FARM-3413
Change-Id: I52330241733a64715f9cfaf94cebdb2deac5f786
commits.subject: Use --entrypoint
